WEBVTT

00:19.352 --> 00:20.353
Come on.

00:27.402 --> 00:29.738
<i>I came to New York
to be a writer.</i>

00:30.238 --> 00:33.241
<i>And sure, some distractions
got in the way.</i>

00:34.367 --> 00:38.413
But I stand before you today
recommitted to my craft.

00:38.913 --> 00:41.750
If given this incredible opportunity,

00:41.750 --> 00:46.337
I am confident that I will be
the discreet, tidy, easygoing,

00:46.337 --> 00:49.549
you'll-never-even-know-I'm-there
roommate

00:49.549 --> 00:51.301
that you've been looking for.

00:52.677 --> 00:54.054
What do you think, Dave?

00:55.388 --> 00:56.514
Sure. Yeah.

00:57.015 --> 00:58.683
- Room is yours.
(gasping) Really?

00:59.225 --> 01:00.977
Oh my god. Great.

01:00.977 --> 01:02.562
Because I've been staying
at the YMCA,

01:02.562 --> 01:04.773
and I'm not sure
what the song is talking about

01:04.773 --> 01:06.858
because "fun" is
definitely not the

01:06.858 --> 01:08.151
first word that comes to mind.

01:08.151 --> 01:10.028
Well, I was just telling
Dave that, uh,

01:10.028 --> 01:12.197
we need some more
female energy here.

01:12.655 --> 01:14.991
